1
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:34,960
[Wind Direction]

2
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:37,950
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:42,289
[Autumn of 1987]

4
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:41,110
Great job!

5
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,440
Kids, think about it.

6
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:46,110
What things do we find in nature?

7
00:01:46,110 --> 00:01:48,630
There's the sky. There are trees...

8
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:52,070
Yaya,

9
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:54,470
you got this wrong.

10
00:01:55,110 --> 00:01:56,950
The lake should be blue,

11
00:01:56,970 --> 00:01:58,690
not pink.

12
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:00,270
Use this.

13
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:03,270
Why does the lake have to be blue?

14
00:02:04,350 --> 00:02:05,630
It's common sense.

15
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:07,700
Have you ever seen a pink lake?

16
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:09,590
A pink lake?

17
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:11,410
Well, I haven't.

18
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:14,830
It doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

19
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:16,579
That's true.

20
00:02:17,950 --> 00:02:18,590
How do you know for sure?

21
00:02:18,590 --> 00:02:19,280
Maybe there's a pink lake

22
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,000
somewhere in the world.

23
00:02:37,710 --> 00:02:40,180
[Good Person]

24
00:02:43,290 --> 00:02:43,810
I should've known

25
00:02:43,810 --> 00:02:45,890
and bought it more sausages.

26
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:47,430
This brand's sausages are tasty.

27
00:02:47,430 --> 00:02:48,630
Even Li Si likes them.

28
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,200
What are you doing here?

29
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:55,200
Wow, that's a big boat!

30
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,520
Is it all yours?

31
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:58,760
It's the village's, not mine.

32
00:02:58,950 --> 00:03:00,150
So, where do you live?

33
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:02,030
On the boat?

34
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:03,900
That sounds fun!

35
00:03:06,110 --> 00:03:06,950
What are you doing?

36
00:03:06,950 --> 00:03:08,070
What are you doing?

37
00:03:08,470 --> 00:03:09,430
I'm already here,

38
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:10,380
so let me come in for a bit.

39
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:11,460
Rest my feet

40
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:12,740
and have some water.

41
00:03:13,070 --> 00:03:14,670
Go back home and drink your water there.

42
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:15,870
Why are you like this?

43
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:16,670
I came all this way,

44
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:18,130
and you're shooing me off.

45
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:18,870
Besides,

46
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:19,710
I have something important

47
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,430
-to tell you.
-I don’t want to hear it.

48
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,150
I haven't said anything yet.

49
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:23,470
-How did you know?
-I don’t want to hear it.

50
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,990
-I don’t want to hear it.
-Xiaowa!

51
00:03:24,990 --> 00:03:25,750
Let go of her.

52
00:03:25,990 --> 00:03:26,750
Grandpa.

53
00:03:27,070 --> 00:03:27,670
Grandpa?

54
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:29,590
Grandpa!

55
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:31,300
Hello, Grandpa!

56
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,300
Let me help you with that.

57
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,270
I'm Cheng Miaomiao,

58
00:03:35,270 --> 00:03:36,829
Qiang Xiaowa's classmate.

59
00:03:36,829 --> 00:03:38,030
I'm here to visit.

60
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,860
-Oh, Xiaowa's classmate?
-Good, good!

61
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:41,790
Good, good!

62
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:43,510
Who invited you here?

63
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,400
Hey, Xiaowa,

64
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:47,670
let your friend in.

65
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,550
I'll make some tea. Come aboard!

66
00:03:49,550 --> 00:03:51,660
Alright, alright. Grandpa said I could.

67
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:53,060
Grandpa, let me help you.

68
00:03:53,410 --> 00:03:54,190
-Be careful.
-No need.

69
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:55,260
Grandpa, be careful.

70
00:03:55,260 --> 00:03:55,820
Come on.

71
00:03:55,990 --> 00:03:57,650
Take a look at our humble home.

72
00:03:58,910 --> 00:04:00,470
Wow, there's a room inside?

73
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:02,750
Have a seat, have a seat.

74
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:05,870
Girl, sit down.

75
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:06,430
Sit.

76
00:04:08,470 --> 00:04:09,550
Ever since Xiaowa

77
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:11,830
started at the oilfield school,

78
00:04:12,380 --> 00:04:13,580
you're the first girl

79
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,040
to come visit our home.

80
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:18,350
Well, Grandpa, I'll visit more often then.

81
00:04:18,350 --> 00:04:19,680
You're always welcome!

82
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:21,160
Stay for dinner tonight.

83
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,680
Thank you, Grandpa.

84
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:26,410
Let me pour you some water.

85
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:27,940
Grandpa.

86
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:29,790
What is this room for?

87
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:32,510
That's a kiln storage room.

88
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:33,909
Go take a look if you want.

89
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,060
You scared me.

90
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:49,710
Grandpa.

91
00:04:50,930 --> 00:04:53,040
Can I check out the upper deck?

92
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:53,870
No.

93
00:04:53,870 --> 00:04:54,990
Why not?

94
00:04:55,790 --> 00:04:57,550
Go on, but be careful.

95
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:00,580
Move over.

96
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,180
What's up there?

97
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:17,340
Do you live here?

98
00:05:20,370 --> 00:05:21,970
There's more up there.

99
00:05:22,110 --> 00:05:23,310
Don't go up.

100
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,610
Why do you care?

101
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,320
Grandpa said I could explore.

102
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:31,310
Wow, this is so cool!

103
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:36,550
Like something out of a movie!

104
00:05:37,909 --> 00:05:39,270
Why are you really here?

105
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:40,550
I came to hang out with you.

106
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:42,260
[Bon Voyage]

107
00:05:42,909 --> 00:05:44,750
Did you catch all these fish?

108
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,050
Can you eat them?

109
00:05:49,350 --> 00:05:51,830
Do you have to go out to sea every day?

110
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:55,150
When it's windy, we can't go out.

111
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:58,240
Can you dive deep

112
00:05:58,270 --> 00:05:59,470
into the ocean floor?

113
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:00,750
No, I can't.

114
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:03,360
At most, one dive will catch a fish.

115
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:04,640
That's impressive.

116
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:12,470
Sea, can you hear me?

117
00:06:12,490 --> 00:06:15,730
My name is Cheng Miaomiao.

118
00:06:19,030 --> 00:06:21,090
It's hard to keep the balance up here.

119
00:06:21,810 --> 00:06:22,780
Yuan Shanqing.

120
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,310
It's me, Cheng Yaya.

121
00:06:32,710 --> 00:06:33,640
Why are you here?

122
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:36,070
I came to see Zi.

123
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,350
Come on in then.

124
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:41,909
Zi.

125
00:06:42,470 --> 00:06:44,070
Look what I brought!

126
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:45,950
I got you

127
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:46,909
a new toy.

128
00:06:46,909 --> 00:06:47,820
It's also my new friend.

129
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:48,909
Its name is Bai.

130
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:49,750
Come on, Bai,

131
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:50,950
say hi to Zi.

132
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:52,350
I'm...

133
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,070
Wow, Zi's going to

134
00:06:54,909 --> 00:06:55,590
hug you.

135
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:56,960
Say something to it.

136
00:06:56,990 --> 00:06:59,390
Hello, my name is Bai.

137
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:02,010
Let me get you a glass of water.

138
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:02,910
Thank you.

139
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:05,950
What?

140
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:09,070
You want to play with crayons?

141
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:10,950
Can you?

142
00:07:13,990 --> 00:07:14,710
Zi?

143
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:17,790
Zi?

144
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:20,390
Bai is talking to you.

145
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:21,430
Can you hear it?

146
00:07:22,030 --> 00:07:23,470
She can't talk yet.

147
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:24,680
She's only two.

148
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:26,790
But most kids can talk

149
00:07:26,790 --> 00:07:27,850
by this age, right?

150
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:30,870
Maybe she's just a bit slow.

151
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:32,600
I've been teaching her.

152
00:07:38,150 --> 00:07:39,550
Don't worry too much.

153
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:41,659
Some kids just talk later.

154
00:07:42,390 --> 00:07:44,000
I remember my mom saying

155
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:45,350
I didn't start speaking properly

156
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:47,110
until after I was almost two and a half.

157
00:07:47,110 --> 00:07:48,150
She even joked that

158
00:07:48,150 --> 00:07:49,630
she gave birth to a fool!

159
00:07:55,790 --> 00:07:56,870
But I'm saying,

160
00:07:56,870 --> 00:07:58,060
I may have spoken late,

161
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:59,150
but I walked early—

162
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:00,910
by the time I was one, I could walk.

163
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:01,910
Unlike my sister,

164
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:02,870
who walked late.

165
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:03,470
Even now, at 17,

166
00:08:03,470 --> 00:08:05,070
she still trips all the time!

167
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:09,570
Zi's fine with walking, though.

168
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:10,850
She started wobbling around

169
00:08:10,850 --> 00:08:12,180
at about one.

170
00:08:12,470 --> 00:08:13,430
Exactly,

171
00:08:13,470 --> 00:08:14,130
every kid

172
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:15,480
develops differently.

173
00:08:16,790 --> 00:08:18,050
Don't stress about it.

174
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:19,110
Here.

175
00:08:20,630 --> 00:08:22,360
Grandpa, this is so delicious!

176
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:23,550
You don't get to eat this often

177
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:25,110
at home, do you?

178
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:27,030
Where would I?

179
00:08:27,870 --> 00:08:30,070
My mom's cooking is awful.

180
00:08:30,130 --> 00:08:32,200
My dad's a little better,

181
00:08:32,230 --> 00:08:33,190
but not by much.

182
00:08:33,230 --> 00:08:34,990
I don't like either of their cooking.

183
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:36,830
Well, eat up if you like it.

184
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,309
These are fish we caught ourselves,

185
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,909
and seafood too—

186
00:08:39,909 --> 00:08:40,909
super fresh.

187
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:42,870
Whenever you want more,

188
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,190
just come by the seaside.

189
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:45,870
Okay, but they used to say

190
00:08:45,870 --> 00:08:46,870
this was a local area,

191
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:49,600
and we weren't allowed to come over. They said...

192
00:08:53,110 --> 00:08:54,710
They said it's the sea,

193
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:57,070
but we don't really know how to swim.

194
00:09:00,310 --> 00:09:00,990
Girl,

195
00:09:01,470 --> 00:09:03,070
I wanted to ask you something.

196
00:09:03,070 --> 00:09:04,630
How's Xiaowa

197
00:09:04,990 --> 00:09:06,070
doing in school?

198
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:08,510
Do the teachers think he's doing alright?

199
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,050
Yeah, he's doing fine!

200
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:11,230
The teachers and students

201
00:09:11,230 --> 00:09:12,430
all really like him.

202
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:14,230
Really?

203
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:16,750
That's great!

204
00:09:18,270 --> 00:09:19,330
Oh right, Grandpa,

205
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,700
our school has some rules.

206
00:09:21,790 --> 00:09:23,190
Like, boys can't

207
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:24,460
have really long hair.

208
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:25,110
Also,

209
00:09:25,110 --> 00:09:26,910
we have to wear the same uniform.

210
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,440
Whatever rules the school has,

211
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,710
we'll follow them.

212
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,330
We can't let the teachers worry about us.

213
00:09:32,590 --> 00:09:34,590
But his hair, ever since he was a kid,

214
00:09:35,030 --> 00:09:37,230
his older brother used to cut it for him.

215
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:37,690
Now that

216
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,430
his brother's been working away for a few years,

217
00:09:39,430 --> 00:09:40,760
no one's around to help.

218
00:09:41,190 --> 00:09:42,630
He's gotten stubborn about it,

219
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:44,430
and won't let anyone else touch his hair.

220
00:09:44,430 --> 00:09:45,990
Isn't it frustrating?

221
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:48,070
I get it.

222
00:09:48,070 --> 00:09:49,390
My little brother's the same way,

223
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:50,630
hates getting his hair cut.

224
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:52,070
Every time it happens,

225
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:53,830
he cries like the world's ending.

226
00:09:53,830 --> 00:09:55,990
In the end, my mom had to cut it for him.

227
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:57,800
They're exactly alike.

228
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,500
But we can't break the school rules.

229
00:10:02,860 --> 00:10:03,720
This time,

230
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:06,020
whether he likes it or not, he's getting it cut.

231
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:07,020
Did you hear that?

232
00:10:08,430 --> 00:10:09,290
Did you hear me?

233
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:12,030
Say something, will you?

234
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:13,680
Speak up!

235
00:10:13,710 --> 00:10:14,420
Grandpa.

236
00:10:15,630 --> 00:10:17,310
Is it just the two of you living here?

237
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:18,570
Where are his parents?

238
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:23,510
I don't have parents.

239
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:32,430
I found Xiaowa

240
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:35,170
and picked him up.

241
00:10:38,470 --> 00:10:40,790
Girl,

242
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:44,510
I'm not well-educated.

243
00:10:44,990 --> 00:10:46,670
I can barely read or write.

244
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:48,330
Teaching Xiaowa is beyond me.

245
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:52,350
I just worry

246
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,470
his stubbornness

247
00:10:54,470 --> 00:10:56,020
will make it hard for him to fit in.

248
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,680
He's not being bullied, is he?

249
00:10:58,270 --> 00:10:59,000
Grandpa.

250
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:00,910
Don't worry.

251
00:11:01,590 --> 00:11:02,770
As long as I'm around,

252
00:11:02,770 --> 00:11:04,130
no one will bully him.

253
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:05,950
I promise

254
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,850
I'll look after Xiaowa.

255
00:11:08,870 --> 00:11:10,470
Good, good,

256
00:11:11,950 --> 00:11:12,870
good.

257
00:11:17,060 --> 00:11:18,780
Girl, eat.

258
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,030
Here.

259
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,530
She goes to bed right after eating?

260
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:39,900
She loves sleeping.

261
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:43,360
You go ahead and eat.

262
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:46,190
I'm not hungry.

263
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,480
Well, I'm hungry!

264
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:57,750
I can make scrambled eggs for you.

265
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:58,950
Wanna try my cooking?

266
00:11:59,310 --> 00:12:00,510
Where are your eggs?

267
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:03,310
We're out of eggs.

268
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:07,950
Go home and eat dinner.

269
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:11,030
It's fine.

270
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,710
I usually just drink milk at night.

271
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:20,310
Grandpa, that's enough.

272
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:21,470
Don't pack more.

273
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:22,510
I can't finish it.

274
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:23,700
If you finish it, come back for more.

275
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:24,950
Don't be shy.

276
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:25,550
Don't worry.

277
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:26,510
I won't!

278
00:12:26,510 --> 00:12:27,150
Here.

279
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:28,590
Okay.

280
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,950
Alright, I'm heading out. See you next time!

281
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:33,700
Okay, walk her out.

282
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:36,110
The sea breeze is strong. Watch your step. Be careful.

283
00:12:36,110 --> 00:12:37,270
Hurry up.

284
00:12:39,340 --> 00:12:41,900
From now on, we are brothers.

285
00:12:42,150 --> 00:12:44,440
Starting tomorrow, I'll teach you Mandarin.

286
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:47,090
Think of this as the tuition fee.

287
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:49,720
Give it to me. I know the way.

288
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:50,920
No need to walk me out.

289
00:12:58,430 --> 00:12:59,430
Wait, wait!

290
00:12:59,430 --> 00:13:00,870
It's not stolen.

291
